<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5823/57: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-17T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>71. Your 138, June 10, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>This Government will agree to suggestion of Swedish Government that
                                Articles 11 and 12 of the Consular Convention of 1910, be eliminated
                                in their entirety. Referring draft of note to Foreign Office
                                suggested in Department instruction No. 644 of April 22, 1920, make
                                necessary changes therein to effect entire elimination of said
                                articles and proceed in accordance with that instruction.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>